reviewText: I love this movie. It took me awhile to find it. I watched it when it was on tv. Danelle Steel is a good writer. I have watched many of her made for tv movies. This one tells of the stories of 3 couples and there lives and the families they want. Which is what live is all about. It's very touching and romantic. It is another good movie to curl up on the couch with. A country girl from MaineDanielle Steel's: Mixed Blessings

i saw Mixed Blessings with Gabrielle Cateris, it makes you feel all warm. inside. Gabrielle Cateris & Scott Baio. are really good actors. if you want to see a real good movie. you should get mixed blessings. you should watch it with somebody you Love!

A good "Saturday afternoon/cuddle-up and crochet" type of movie.  It shows that families can be formed in many ways and that "traditional" families are not the "norm" anymore.  It is thought provoking in some ways (nothing heavy)and let couples and individuals know that there are more than one way to have a family.  It also sheds so light on adopting older children.  "Older" does not mean damaged...
Love it

This is pretty much soapy trash starring an eclectic group of TV stars. Your enjoyment may depend on one or more of the stars being actors you like to watch which was the case for me. This was the only reason I purchased the movie. Lots of emotional angst and troubled affairs for several pairs of lovers.
